  "Moroccan hospitality has a strong cultural foundation — warmth, generosity, and attention to guests are deeply ingrained values. I would build on this foundation: 1) Technical skills — housekeeping standards, F&B service protocols, front desk operations using modern PMS (Opera, Fidelio). 2) Soft skills — guest communication in Arabic, French, English, and Spanish, anticipating needs, and handling VIP guests. 3) Cultural intelligence — understanding the customs and expectations of different tourist nationalities (European, Gulf, Asian). 4) Service recovery — empowering staff to resolve complaints immediately (up to certain value). 5) Continuous training — monthly workshops, cross-department rotation, and online learning via ISIT (Institut Supérieur International du Tourisme) modules. Performance metrics: guest satisfaction scores (NPS), TripAdvisor ratings, and mystery guest evaluations. Career progression paths reduce turnover in an industry with traditionally high staff rotation.",
  "L'hospitalité marocaine a une forte base culturelle — chaleur, générosité et attention aux invités. Je construirais sur cette base : 1) Compétences techniques — standards de ménage, protocoles de service F&B, réception avec PMS modernes. 2) Soft skills — communication en arabe, français, anglais et espagnol, anticipation des besoins. 3) Intelligence culturelle — comprendre les attentes de différentes nationalités. 4) Récupération de service — habiliter le personnel à résoudre les plaintes. 5) Formation continue — ateliers mensuels, rotation inter-départements et modules ISIT. Métriques : NPS, notes TripAdvisor et client mystère. Les parcours de carrière réduisent le turnover.",
